# Privacy Policy

**Effective date:** April 21, 2026

---

## 1. Who We Are

Tabulus is an iOS app built and operated by Robert Fusting, a solo developer.

**Contact:** robertmfusting@gmail.com

---

## 2. Information We Collect

### Information You Provide Directly

- **Account:** Username, email, password (email signup) — or Apple ID and optional email (Sign in with Apple)
- **Profile:** Optional profile image
- **Content you post:** Reviews, ratings, game night entries (games played, participants, outcomes), photos (up to 5 per upload, 8MB each)
- **Social graph:** Friend requests you send/accept
- **Reports:** Reports you submit on other users' content

### Information Collected Automatically

- Authentication tokens (to keep you signed in)
- Server logs (IP address, timestamps, request paths) used for real-time debugging only and not retained

**We do NOT collect:** Location, contacts, analytics, crash reports, advertising identifiers, or any third-party tracking.

---

## 3. How We Use Your Information

- Operate the app (accounts, posting, feeds, friends)
- Authenticate you and maintain your session
- Send password reset emails
- Enforce platform rules (respond to reports)
- Secure the service (abuse prevention, debugging)

---

## 4. How Your Data Is Stored

- Backend hosted on Microsoft Azure (Azure Container Apps, West US 2 region)
- Images stored in Azure Blob Storage and served via short-lived signed URLs
- Passwords are hashed using Argon2 and never stored in plaintext
- Refresh tokens are stored securely in the iOS Keychain on your device

---

## 5. Third Parties

We share data only with infrastructure providers necessary to operate the app:

- **Microsoft Azure** — Hosting, database, image storage, and transactional email (Azure Communication Services) for password resets  
- **Apple** — Authentication when using Sign in with Apple  
- **BoardGameGeek** — Game metadata is fetched server-side; no user data is shared  

We do **not** sell or share your data for advertising and do not use analytics or tracking SDKs.

---

## 6. Your Choices and Rights

- Only friends can view your game nights  
- Remove friends via the Friends tab — this revokes mutual access to game night content  
- Block users to remove them as friends and stop seeing their content  
- Edit your profile within the app  
- Delete game nights via the ellipsis menu on any game night card  
- Delete reviews via the delete button on the associated board game page  
- Delete your account in-app (**Settings → Delete Account**)  
  - This permanently removes your account and all associated content  
- **Access/export your data:** Email robertmfusting@gmail.com  
- Reset your password via the "Forgot Password" flow on the login page  

---

## 7. Content Moderation

- Game Nights and Reviews include a report/block option via the ellipsis menu  
- Blocked users’ content is no longer visible to you  
- Reported content is hidden from your view  
- Content with 3 or more reports may be removed  
- Reports are reviewed manually every 24 hours by Robert Fusting  

---

## 8. Children

Tabulus is not intended for children under 13, and we do not knowingly collect their information.

If you believe a child has created an account, contact: robertmfusting@gmail.com

---

## 9. Data Retention

- Data is retained while your account is active  
- Upon account deletion, your profile, reviews, game nights, and images are removed from live systems  
- Deleted data may remain in encrypted backups for up to 7 days before automatic deletion  

---

## 10. Security

We use:

- HTTPS for all network traffic  
- Hashed passwords  
- Token-based authentication  
- Secure storage via iOS Keychain  

No method of transmission or storage is completely secure. While we use commercially reasonable safeguards, we cannot guarantee absolute security.

---

## 11. Changes

We may update this policy periodically. Material changes will be posted here with a revised effective date.

